WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.675 --> 00:00:09.677
[theme music playing]

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

3
00:01:58.244 --> 00:02:00.246
[dragons roaring]

4
00:02:05.585 --> 00:02:07.587
[Syrax growls]

5
00:02:09.464 --> 00:02:11.966
[Seasmoke screeching]

6
00:02:24.270 --> 00:02:26.314
[roaring]

7
00:02:33.029 --> 00:02:37.533
You stand before the queen
of the Seven Kingdoms...

8
00:02:39.035 --> 00:02:41.954
with a dragon of House Targaryen.

9
00:02:43.373 --> 00:02:45.124
I had no design upon it!

10
00:02:45.583 --> 00:02:47.001
What do you want?

11
00:02:48.836 --> 00:02:51.089
To learn the ways of dragonriders.

12
00:02:53.091 --> 00:02:54.675
And to serve my queen.

13
00:02:56.761 --> 00:02:57.845
Your Grace.

14
00:02:59.013 --> 00:03:01.015
[dragons growling]

15
00:03:10.274 --> 00:03:12.276
[bellowing]

16
00:03:17.407 --> 00:03:19.409
[roaring]

17
00:03:26.207 --> 00:03:30.920
You kneel quickly
for a man so suddenly elevated.

18
00:03:31.796 --> 00:03:35.466
This dragon came to me. not I to him.

19
00:03:35.550 --> 00:03:37.718
[Seasmoke screeches]

20
00:03:37.802 --> 00:03:40.847
I have sweated blood
in service of House Velaryon.

21
00:03:41.848 --> 00:03:46.811
I may appear lowborn.
but I know much and more of service.

22
00:03:48.938 --> 00:03:52.567
And if the gods call me to greater things.
who am I to refuse them?

23
00:03:55.987 --> 00:03:57.697
[Seasmoke growling]

24
00:04:02.243 --> 00:04:03.327
Stand.

25
00:04:11.878 --> 00:04:13.421
What is your parentage?

26
00:04:13.504 --> 00:04:15.214
My mother was a shipwright.

27
00:04:16.716 --> 00:04:17.884
My father is

28
00:04:19.218 --> 00:04:20.678
no one of consequence.

29
00:04:21.888 --> 00:04:24.932
Your ancestors? Any of House Targaryen?

30
00:04:25.016 --> 00:04:27.768
We're not the sort of family
to keep annals. Your Grace.

31
00:04:30.480 --> 00:04:31.564
What is your name?

32
00:04:32.148 --> 00:04:34.567
Addam. Of Hull.

33
00:04:38.196 --> 00:04:40.198
[Seasmoke growling]

34
00:04:43.284 --> 00:04:44.911
You have done something...

35
00:04:46.746 --> 00:04:48.372
I feared impossible...

36
00:04:50.416 --> 00:04:51.751
Addam of Hull.

37
00:04:57.048 --> 00:04:58.382
I am glad of it.

38
00:05:03.221 --> 00:05:05.306
Do you think you can get him
to Dragonstone?

39
00:05:08.392 --> 00:05:09.393
I can try.

40
00:05:16.192 --> 00:05:17.360
[Alicent] All my life.

41
00:05:18.319 --> 00:05:21.822
I have endeavored
to serve both my house and the realm.

42
00:05:23.658 --> 00:05:25.535
And somehow none of it matters.

43
00:05:28.037 --> 00:05:29.413
We are cast aside.

44
00:05:31.874 --> 00:05:32.917
Or hated.

45
00:05:36.504 --> 00:05:38.130
You'll have a scar.

46
00:05:39.215 --> 00:05:41.884
but it will be easily hidden.

47
00:05:43.094 --> 00:05:44.762
[rat squeaking]

48
00:05:47.682 --> 00:05:49.016
Nothing is clean here.

49
00:05:59.318 --> 00:06:01.112
I wish to go out. Ser Rickard.

50
00:06:02.113 --> 00:06:03.155
Out?

51
00:06:04.156 --> 00:06:05.741
To the Kingswood. I think.

52
00:06:05.825 --> 00:06:07.785
Then I'll have
the stewards prepare a retinue.

53
00:06:07.868 --> 00:06:08.869
No retinue.

54
00:06:09.745 --> 00:06:11.747
- Then your handmaidens.
- No handmaidens.

55
00:06:13.624 --> 00:06:14.709
Just you.

56
00:06:21.716 --> 00:06:23.718
[indistinct chatter]

57
00:06:24.510 --> 00:06:27.179
[Ironrod] What are they for?
The block or the crow cage?

58
00:06:28.347 --> 00:06:29.390
The Wall.

59
00:06:30.808 --> 00:06:32.602
The prince regent is merciful.

60
00:06:32.685 --> 00:06:33.769
Hmm.

61
00:06:35.646 --> 00:06:38.232
Well. they started a riot.

62
00:06:38.316 --> 00:06:40.651
Justice is served. I suppose.

63
00:06:48.701 --> 00:06:51.912
I have received word
of a matter of great importance.

64
00:06:53.289 --> 00:06:56.000
Rumor of a sighting
of the dragon Seasmoke...

65
00:06:57.293 --> 00:06:58.419
with a rider.

66
00:07:00.087 --> 00:07:02.089
A fine piece of intelligence.

67
00:07:02.173 --> 00:07:06.052
And now you seek favor
by delivering it to Prince Aemond.

68
00:07:06.135 --> 00:07:09.513
Actually. I thought I might seek
your advice. Lord Larys.

69
00:07:10.097 --> 00:07:11.807
Whispers being your province.

70
00:07:12.642 --> 00:07:15.978
[guard] Kneel before the Prince Regent
Aemond Targaryen.

71
00:07:16.771 --> 00:07:20.858
Oh. but this is your whisper.
Lord Jasper. not mine.

72
00:07:21.609 --> 00:07:25.988
[Ironrod] But if you consider it valuable.
perhaps you could deliver it

73
00:07:26.697 --> 00:07:29.241
and find favor with Aemond yourself.

74
00:07:29.325 --> 00:07:31.410
[Aemond] You will forsake
your white cloaks for black

75
00:07:31.494 --> 00:07:34.330
and serve out your days at the Wall.

76
00:07:34.413 --> 00:07:35.623
[Larys] Who is this rider?

77
00:07:36.499 --> 00:07:39.335
[Ironrod] That is less clear.

78
00:07:39.418 --> 00:07:43.589
But it must surely be the Lady Rhaena.
She has wanted for a dragon all her life.

79
00:07:43.673 --> 00:07:46.509
Indeed. but she tried already
when she was four-and-ten.

80
00:07:46.592 --> 00:07:49.261
The beast Seasmoke very nearly
devoured her. Who else?

81
00:07:51.472 --> 00:07:53.516
Yes. it is a shallow pool.

82
00:07:54.141 --> 00:07:55.309
Where did you hear it?

83
00:07:56.102 --> 00:07:57.103
My squire.

84
00:07:59.146 --> 00:08:01.315
He heard it from the stable hand.

85
00:08:01.399 --> 00:08:04.151
who heard it from his father.
a fisherman

86
00:08:05.152 --> 00:08:07.405
whose shipmate claims he saw it.

87
00:08:08.656 --> 00:08:09.656
Oh.

88
00:08:13.369 --> 00:08:17.832
You are of course welcome to bring
this news to the prince regent. but. um...

89
00:08:19.166 --> 00:08:22.294
perhaps this is one of those whispers
best left to the wind.

90
00:08:29.927 --> 00:08:31.178
[Ironrod clears throat]

91
00:08:44.859 --> 00:08:47.069
[dramatic music playing]

92
00:09:02.960 --> 00:09:03.961
The queen is unharmed.

93
00:09:04.044 --> 00:09:05.045
[sighs]

94
00:09:05.129 --> 00:09:07.089
[Corlys] What of the rider?
Do we know who he is?

95
00:09:07.965 --> 00:09:11.552
He appears to be a shipwright
in your employ. Lord Hand.

96
00:09:11.635 --> 00:09:13.095
[Bartimos] A commoner?

97
00:09:13.179 --> 00:09:15.723
With respect to your workers. Lord Corlys.

98
00:09:15.806 --> 00:09:19.810
the lowborn cannot go around
seizing dragons.

99
00:09:19.894 --> 00:09:21.896
Has the thief been secured?

100
00:09:21.979 --> 00:09:25.357
[Gerardys] Her Grace has commanded
that he remain here as a guest.

101
00:09:25.441 --> 00:09:29.278
She wishes him to be instructed
in the art of dragonriding

102
00:09:29.361 --> 00:09:31.697
and that I should teach him
some High Valyrian.

103
00:09:32.364 --> 00:09:36.285
We know nothing about this man.
save that he is lowborn.

104
00:09:36.368 --> 00:09:38.162
What say you. Lord Hand?

105
00:09:40.122 --> 00:09:44.543
We will await the queen's accounting
before passing judgment.

106
00:09:44.627 --> 00:09:45.669
[sighs]

107
00:09:48.130 --> 00:09:49.548
Where is the queen?

108
00:09:51.675 --> 00:09:53.928
[Lorent] Her Grace sends word
she will not be attending.

109
00:09:58.557 --> 00:10:01.101
[Mysaria]
<i>So he serves you and not himself.</i>

110
00:10:01.185 --> 00:10:02.353
That is lucky.

111
00:10:02.436 --> 00:10:05.564
Lucky? Or somehow ordained?

112
00:10:06.398 --> 00:10:10.611
Seasmoke chose him. He surely has
Targaryen blood in him somewhere.

113
00:10:11.362 --> 00:10:13.739
The dragon must sense it.
There will be others.

114
00:10:13.823 --> 00:10:15.825
We will find riders
for Vermithor and Silverwing.

115
00:10:15.908 --> 00:10:17.284
You trust this man?

116
00:10:18.327 --> 00:10:21.080
What choice do I have? He has a dragon.

117
00:10:21.163 --> 00:10:24.583
Without him. I have only Syrax
who may give Aemond a second thought.

118
00:10:25.668 --> 00:10:27.545
The question is where to look.

119
00:10:28.170 --> 00:10:32.174
Targaryen blood was perhaps too thin
in Ser Steffon Darklyn.

120
00:10:32.258 --> 00:10:34.885
If I can find others
with a more direct line of breeding...

121
00:10:34.969 --> 00:10:36.387
[Mysaria chuckles]

122
00:10:37.638 --> 00:10:39.098
Forgive me. Your Grace.

123
00:10:41.934 --> 00:10:46.146
But you are better served looking
under the sheets and in the woodpiles.

124
00:10:50.276 --> 00:10:54.864
I once worked in a pleasure house
where generations of Targaryen princelings

125
00:10:54.947 --> 00:10:56.407
had their revels.

126
00:10:56.490 --> 00:11:01.579
There are fourscore of their bastard
progeny. at least that are known to me.

127
00:11:01.662 --> 00:11:05.749
There are sure to be more.
perhaps some here on Dragonstone.

128
00:11:05.833 --> 00:11:08.711
the misbegotten offspring of your house.

129
00:11:19.179 --> 00:11:20.639
You speak of the lowborn.

130
00:11:20.723 --> 00:11:25.102
They are as like to serve you
as highborn lords or ladies. perhaps more.

131
00:11:28.230 --> 00:11:33.819
But in the highborn houses.
there is... an ancient fealty.

132
00:11:34.820 --> 00:11:35.863
There is honor.

133
00:11:36.989 --> 00:11:40.367
Your royal half-brothers.
Aegon and Aemond.

134
00:11:40.451 --> 00:11:45.080
whose blood is pure. who wage war
against you for your throne.

135
00:11:46.290 --> 00:11:47.791
Are they bound by honor?

136
00:11:53.589 --> 00:11:59.553
A common shipwright vows to serve you
while your brothers seek to destroy you.

137
00:12:01.972 --> 00:12:05.476
The order of things has changed.
Your Grace.

138
00:12:06.852 --> 00:12:08.270
Why not embrace it?

139
00:12:18.572 --> 00:12:24.620
For 20 years. the lords of this realm
levied insults at my sons behind my back.

140
00:12:32.753 --> 00:12:33.754
Well then.

141
00:12:35.297 --> 00:12:37.967
let us raise an army of bastards.

142
00:12:59.405 --> 00:13:00.447
My lord.

143
00:13:00.531 --> 00:13:01.532
"My lord"?

144
00:13:02.616 --> 00:13:04.410
How you have come up in the world.

145
00:13:07.246 --> 00:13:10.833
I wish to ask for leave to relinquish
my part as a shipwright in your service.

146
00:13:11.542 --> 00:13:14.211
There are good men. and strong.
who can take my place.

147
00:13:19.133 --> 00:13:20.467
Your leave is granted.

148
00:13:33.355 --> 00:13:34.356
Well done.

149
00:13:41.321 --> 00:13:43.323
[ominous music playing]

150
00:14:01.467 --> 00:14:02.760
[knocking on door]

151
00:14:03.594 --> 00:14:05.554
[Simon] Lord Tully
has answered your summons

152
00:14:05.637 --> 00:14:07.848
and brought the Riverlords. my king.

153
00:14:13.812 --> 00:14:16.052
[Daemon] My condolences
on the passing of your grandsire.

154
00:14:16.690 --> 00:14:19.650
But the crown congratulates you on
your ascension to the head of your house

155
00:14:19.693 --> 00:14:22.696
and lord paramount in the Riverlands.
Truly glorious. well done.

156
00:14:23.781 --> 00:14:24.823
I did nothing.

157
00:14:24.907 --> 00:14:28.160
Nevertheless. you are here.
which is the important thing.

158
00:14:28.243 --> 00:14:30.079
You were quick enough
to dismiss me before.

159
00:14:30.162 --> 00:14:33.540
You were of no significance
to me then. But now...

160
00:14:36.543 --> 00:14:38.378
I shall have my great host.

161
00:14:39.963 --> 00:14:41.673
You have a decision to make.

162
00:14:42.591 --> 00:14:45.344
I presume it is clear to you
which is the right one.

163
00:14:45.427 --> 00:14:47.262
You will forgive me. Your Grace.

164
00:14:47.346 --> 00:14:52.142
I am green in this sort of matter.
as you so kindly point out. but...

165
00:14:54.311 --> 00:14:57.731
it does seem to me
that you've made rather a mess here.

166
00:14:57.815 --> 00:15:00.943
countenancing barbarities
in the queen's name.

167
00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:03.278
Whose side are you on?

168
00:15:06.073 --> 00:15:08.283
[breathes deeply]

169
00:15:08.408 --> 00:15:10.911
The Riverlands are held together by oaths.

170
00:15:13.080 --> 00:15:16.333
House Tully swore an oath to King Viserys.

171
00:15:18.544 --> 00:15:22.256
We recognize the authority
of the named heir. Queen Rhaenyra.

172
00:15:22.923 --> 00:15:26.510
and your own... as her king consort.

173
00:15:27.886 --> 00:15:28.887
Good.

174
00:15:30.139 --> 00:15:33.308
Then we shall go to face your vassals
and you will call your banners to war.

175
00:15:33.392 --> 00:15:35.102
That might be difficult. my king.

176
00:15:40.774 --> 00:15:41.775
Well...

177
00:15:43.485 --> 00:15:47.364
I was told they would come to heel
when House Tully declared its allegiance.

178
00:15:47.447 --> 00:15:50.534
That may be the case.
though it is yet to be seen

179
00:15:50.617 --> 00:15:53.745
that they will heed my authority.
as young as it is.

180
00:15:56.081 --> 00:15:57.875
And there is another problem.

181
00:16:00.169 --> 00:16:01.253
They all hate you.

182
00:16:05.299 --> 00:16:08.719
I don't need their love.
I need their swords.

183
00:16:09.344 --> 00:16:10.679
[door opens]

184
00:16:11.722 --> 00:16:17.561
Your Grace. my lord. the Riverlords await.
I fear we cannot delay them any longer.

185
00:16:24.860 --> 00:16:26.361
[Daemon] Come along. Lord Oscar.

186
00:16:31.033 --> 00:16:33.035
[dramatic music playing]

187
00:16:49.343 --> 00:16:51.929
In the deepest darkness comes the dawn.

188
00:16:52.763 --> 00:16:55.098
A new lord. a new beginning.

189
00:16:56.934 --> 00:16:59.478
Let us put all the old unpleasantness
behind us.

190
00:17:05.609 --> 00:17:07.319
Be welcome. my lords.

191
00:17:08.779 --> 00:17:11.281
And you have my thanks
for answering my summons.

192
00:17:11.949 --> 00:17:14.618
I know I'm not the man my grandsire was.

193
00:17:14.701 --> 00:17:18.830
but I hope to begin well
and go on from there.

194
00:17:19.456 --> 00:17:20.832
[Daemon] Well said.

195
00:17:20.916 --> 00:17:22.251
One thing is clear.

196
00:17:23.377 --> 00:17:26.463
The Rivermen honor the old ways
and abide by tradition.

197
00:17:26.546 --> 00:17:28.465
Here. then. is tradition.

198
00:17:28.548 --> 00:17:31.927
Grover Tully is dead.
Lord Oscar raised up in his place.

199
00:17:32.678 --> 00:17:35.555
You have been summoned here
to swear anew your fealty to him.

200
00:17:35.639 --> 00:17:39.476
and as his bannermen. answer his call.

201
00:17:39.559 --> 00:17:41.728
And what would that call be?

202
00:17:41.812 --> 00:17:45.274
In his wisdom. he has pledged
his house and yours to me.

203
00:17:45.357 --> 00:17:47.609
[Riverlords murmuring]

204
00:17:47.693 --> 00:17:50.821
[Riverlord] Lord Oscar.
for generations we have been guided

205
00:17:50.904 --> 00:17:52.990
by the judgment of your forebears.

206
00:17:53.573 --> 00:17:57.119
Why should we now follow a boy
younger than my own sons

207
00:17:57.202 --> 00:18:00.914
when you will align with one who will
desecrate the innocent to reach his aims?

208
00:18:02.082 --> 00:18:04.960
I did only what was necessary. my lord.

209
00:18:06.461 --> 00:18:10.924
And I now deliver to you
the traitor Amos Bracken and his son.

210
00:18:11.008 --> 00:18:13.802
No more traitor to his land than you.
Willem Blackwood.

211
00:18:14.970 --> 00:18:19.933
I take to heart your words. Lord Piper.
And I agree. I am young.

212
00:18:23.645 --> 00:18:26.773
And I have no love for Daemon Targaryen.

213
00:18:26.857 --> 00:18:32.279
He has dishonored himself and the crown
with his... comportment here.

214
00:18:34.072 --> 00:18:37.951
Nevertheless. having so little experience
to guide me.

215
00:18:38.035 --> 00:18:42.956
my best course is to defer to the oath
my grandsire swore to King Viserys

216
00:18:43.040 --> 00:18:45.083
when he named Rhaenyra his heir.

217
00:18:48.837 --> 00:18:51.465
I see no reason to cast aside loyalty.

218
00:18:52.299 --> 00:18:55.969
no matter how loathsome
I may find her representative. the prince.

219
00:18:56.053 --> 00:18:57.095
"King."

220
00:18:58.263 --> 00:19:00.057
Mind your tongue. boy.

221
00:19:01.600 --> 00:19:03.101
[Riverlords murmuring]

222
00:19:12.110 --> 00:19:14.446
Will you have our army or not?

223
00:19:25.165 --> 00:19:27.042
I am. in the end. a Riverman.

224
00:19:27.834 --> 00:19:29.920
and the word of my house stands.

225
00:19:30.003 --> 00:19:32.798
even if certain people are unworthy of it.

226
00:19:40.639 --> 00:19:42.682
Your Lord Oscar is bold.

227
00:19:44.351 --> 00:19:46.228
But he is perhaps not wrong.

228
00:19:47.771 --> 00:19:51.858
I may have been a touch enthusiastic
in pursuing my aims.

229
00:19:53.527 --> 00:20:00.033
But don't allow my failings to keep you
from supporting an upright man.

230
00:20:00.117 --> 00:20:04.496
Lord Oscar. we honor the old ways.
as Prince Daemon says.

231
00:20:05.330 --> 00:20:08.041
And the old ways call for justice
to be done.

232
00:20:08.125 --> 00:20:10.252
- [Piper] Yes!
- Justice has been done.

233
00:20:11.211 --> 00:20:14.923
They who bent the knee to the usurper
have been brought to heel.

234
00:20:16.299 --> 00:20:20.637
And now. we unite before our liege lord...

235
00:20:22.514 --> 00:20:24.266
and our king consort.

236
00:20:39.030 --> 00:20:42.242
I accept you as my vassal.
Willem Blackwood.

237
00:20:49.875 --> 00:20:50.876
But...

238
00:20:52.586 --> 00:20:55.505
I am lord paramount of all River Houses.

239
00:20:57.716 --> 00:21:00.969
There is only one answer for the crimes
you visited upon your neighbors.

240
00:21:05.182 --> 00:21:09.352
I did only what His Grace the king
required of me.

241
00:21:09.436 --> 00:21:12.189
[Oscar] It is true that he made clear
his base desires.

242
00:21:12.814 --> 00:21:15.525
but you did not have to pursue
such savagery.

243
00:21:17.402 --> 00:21:21.072
You did it because you wanted to.

244
00:21:21.156 --> 00:21:23.492
Our young lord speaks truly.

245
00:21:25.410 --> 00:21:26.578
Seize him.

246
00:21:26.661 --> 00:21:27.913
[Riverlords murmuring]

247
00:21:28.955 --> 00:21:30.749
[Willem] You can't fucking do this.

248
00:21:32.626 --> 00:21:34.878
Your Grace. command them.
I have only served you.

249
00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:41.343
Command them.

250
00:21:41.426 --> 00:21:44.846
If His Grace wishes
to show contrition for his acts

251
00:21:44.930 --> 00:21:47.849
and to prove himself
deserving of our banners...

252
00:21:49.309 --> 00:21:51.895
he must now rectify his grievous error.

253
00:21:51.978 --> 00:21:53.897
Denounce your crimes...

254
00:21:55.649 --> 00:21:58.026
and dispense justice.

255
00:21:59.903 --> 00:22:00.904
Oh. dear.

256
00:22:00.987 --> 00:22:02.989
[eerie sounds]

257
00:22:03.073 --> 00:22:05.242
[unsettling music playing]

258
00:22:14.125 --> 00:22:15.418
No. no! No!

259
00:22:16.586 --> 00:22:19.589
I did as you asked. Your Grace!
I have been faithful.

260
00:22:32.727 --> 00:22:34.729
[wind whistling]

261
00:22:40.235 --> 00:22:42.237
[unsettling music playing]

262
00:22:44.698 --> 00:22:46.074
[goat bleating]

263
00:22:58.336 --> 00:23:00.005
[man breathing heavily]

264
00:23:39.169 --> 00:23:40.170
What is this?

265
00:23:42.839 --> 00:23:44.382
I never wanted it.

266
00:23:47.886 --> 00:23:49.179
I was right not to.

267
00:23:53.933 --> 00:23:55.894
All that pain it caused.

268
00:24:00.190 --> 00:24:02.651
It crushes whoever wears it.

269
00:24:07.447 --> 00:24:09.449
You always wanted it. Daemon.

270
00:24:15.580 --> 00:24:17.040
Do you want it still?

271
00:24:18.833 --> 00:24:20.835
[high-pitched ringing]

272
00:24:27.634 --> 00:24:29.594
- [Aegon grunting]
- [Orwyle] Slowly. Slowly.

273
00:24:31.846 --> 00:24:32.846
[Aegon groans]

274
00:24:33.640 --> 00:24:34.724
I can't.

275
00:24:34.808 --> 00:24:36.810
You can. You must try. Your Grace.

276
00:24:39.145 --> 00:24:40.313
[Aegon groans]

277
00:24:42.440 --> 00:24:43.733
- [cane snaps]
- [Aegon grunts]

278
00:24:43.817 --> 00:24:46.027
[crying in pain]

279
00:24:46.111 --> 00:24:48.279
I can't! I can't!

280
00:24:48.363 --> 00:24:50.532
[groaning]

281
00:24:53.159 --> 00:24:55.036
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Your Grace.

282
00:24:55.120 --> 00:24:58.331
- [sobbing] Oh. God. Oh. God.
- [knocking on door]

283
00:24:58.415 --> 00:24:59.749
- [yells]
- [Orwyle] A moment!

284
00:24:59.833 --> 00:25:02.210
- [knocking continues]
- A moment. please!

285
00:25:02.293 --> 00:25:03.211
[door opens]

286
00:25:03.212 --> 00:25:05.004
[groaning]

287
00:25:06.339 --> 00:25:09.843
You really oughtn't to be
doing that alone. Grand Maester.

288
00:25:09.926 --> 00:25:11.970
[groaning]

289
00:25:17.934 --> 00:25:18.935
Allow me.

290
00:25:19.602 --> 00:25:21.730
[Aegon groaning]

291
00:25:21.813 --> 00:25:23.189
No. no. no.

292
00:25:23.273 --> 00:25:25.191
- [whimpers]
- [Orwyle] Forgive me. Your Grace.

293
00:25:26.484 --> 00:25:28.611
[grunts. then yells]

294
00:25:37.120 --> 00:25:38.705
- Careful.
- Wait. wait.

295
00:25:39.497 --> 00:25:41.541
[yelling]

296
00:25:41.624 --> 00:25:42.959
Oh. no. no. no!

297
00:25:44.669 --> 00:25:46.504
[groaning]

298
00:25:47.088 --> 00:25:48.590
[breathing heavily]

299
00:25:50.008 --> 00:25:51.676
Your progress is impressive.

300
00:25:54.095 --> 00:25:57.307
But I'm afraid you must work harder.

301
00:25:59.476 --> 00:26:01.436
Your strength will return.

302
00:26:01.519 --> 00:26:05.482
There are adjustments
to the gait and so forth

303
00:26:05.565 --> 00:26:07.567
that you will learn now that you are...

304
00:26:09.527 --> 00:26:10.528
as you are.

305
00:26:10.612 --> 00:26:11.780
[breathing heavily]

306
00:26:23.666 --> 00:26:25.043
You should be more cautious.

307
00:26:26.169 --> 00:26:28.046
Aye. I should. Lord Larys.

308
00:26:28.713 --> 00:26:31.132
He needs rest. He should be abed.

309
00:26:31.216 --> 00:26:33.343
I push him on your instruction.

310
00:26:34.010 --> 00:26:35.804
I'll have the sentry give you
more warning.

311
00:26:38.515 --> 00:26:41.601
- Let him try again in a few hours.
- He is spent.

312
00:26:45.063 --> 00:26:47.273
It will be long
before he may rest again.

313
00:26:47.357 --> 00:26:49.651
[Aegon breathing heavily]

314
00:26:52.570 --> 00:26:53.780
[Aegon groans]

315
00:26:54.489 --> 00:26:56.491
[indistinct chatter]

316
00:26:59.786 --> 00:27:00.787
[Corlys] Alyn.

317
00:27:04.499 --> 00:27:05.583
My lord.

318
00:27:08.962 --> 00:27:11.714
[Corlys] I have tasks
that need your personal attention.

319
00:27:11.798 --> 00:27:14.759
The queen requires ships
at her service in King's Landing.

320
00:27:14.843 --> 00:27:17.595
Charter fishing vessels
and pay whatever they demand.

321
00:27:17.679 --> 00:27:20.181
but ensure their captains
are dependable.

322
00:27:23.059 --> 00:27:25.478
- Put trusted swords aboard.
- Yes. m'lord.

323
00:27:25.562 --> 00:27:27.272
Have them wait just outside
the harbor.

324
00:27:27.355 --> 00:27:29.774
and there will be a message to carry
to one she will name.

325
00:27:37.073 --> 00:27:40.827
The queen has found a new rider
for one of her dragons.

326
00:27:42.036 --> 00:27:43.079
I've heard tell of it.

327
00:27:44.455 --> 00:27:45.623
The rider is your brother.

328
00:27:50.336 --> 00:27:52.672
She now makes the call for others.

329
00:27:53.464 --> 00:27:58.761
Our people are of Old Valyria.
but we are not dragonlords.

330
00:28:00.763 --> 00:28:05.602
I confess I knew little
of your mother's heritage.

331
00:28:08.229 --> 00:28:09.689
If it is...

332
00:28:11.024 --> 00:28:12.567
something in the blood...

333
00:28:17.864 --> 00:28:22.452
My brother was ever restless.
yearning for some sign of his worth.

334
00:28:24.454 --> 00:28:28.833
I am of salt and sea.
I yearn for nothing else.

335
00:28:39.010 --> 00:28:41.012
[wind whistling]

336
00:28:41.095 --> 00:28:43.097
[melancholy music playing]

337
00:29:24.806 --> 00:29:26.808
[music turns suspenseful]

338
00:30:13.730 --> 00:30:14.939
[horse snorts]

339
00:30:31.164 --> 00:30:33.166
I will retire now. Ser Rickard.

340
00:30:40.715 --> 00:30:43.009
When does Your Grace mean
to return to the city?

341
00:30:46.012 --> 00:30:47.513
I'm not yet certain I do.

342
00:30:49.682 --> 00:30:50.725
Good night.

343
00:30:59.442 --> 00:31:01.736
[Jace] The lowborn claiming dragons?

344
00:31:02.570 --> 00:31:06.324
Was it her idea? The Lady Mysaria?

345
00:31:06.407 --> 00:31:09.327
You were enthusiastic enough
when Ser Steffon made his claim.

346
00:31:09.410 --> 00:31:12.747
He was the Lord Commander
of your Queensguard. heir to the Dun Fort.

347
00:31:12.830 --> 00:31:15.249
- These people are...
- Courageous.

348
00:31:15.875 --> 00:31:17.210
Mongrels!

349
00:31:23.299 --> 00:31:24.300
Jace.

350
00:31:27.637 --> 00:31:29.013
Think what is at stake.

351
00:31:29.680 --> 00:31:31.724
I know well what is at stake.

352
00:31:34.685 --> 00:31:36.646
House Targaryen is the blood
of the dragon.

353
00:31:37.313 --> 00:31:40.149
If any may lay claim to it.
what are we then?

354
00:31:40.233 --> 00:31:42.819
The rightful rulers
of the Seven Kingdoms.

355
00:31:43.903 --> 00:31:47.448
And what if one of your baseborn.
silver-haired dragonriders

356
00:31:47.532 --> 00:31:50.076
decides he wants to rule
the Seven Kingdoms?

357
00:31:50.159 --> 00:31:52.078
Did the Conqueror's Dream
foretell that?

358
00:31:53.746 --> 00:31:55.957
What else would you have me do?

359
00:31:58.417 --> 00:32:02.004
Prosecute a war which we will lose.
in which thousands will die?

360
00:32:02.755 --> 00:32:04.507
Fly against Vhagar myself?

361
00:32:04.590 --> 00:32:08.052
Or perhaps you will fly against her
on Vermax.

362
00:32:10.888 --> 00:32:14.976
Jace. with these riders.
we can end a needless war.

363
00:32:16.936 --> 00:32:19.230
I may take my rightful place
on my father's throne.

364
00:32:19.313 --> 00:32:20.439
And when you die?

365
00:32:25.278 --> 00:32:27.238
[scoffs] You are my heir.

366
00:32:41.377 --> 00:32:43.754
Did you think I would have dark hair?

367
00:32:51.929 --> 00:32:54.307
When you took Harwin Strong
into your bed.

368
00:32:54.390 --> 00:32:57.268
did you think I might favor him.
or did it not cross your mind?

369
00:32:59.896 --> 00:33:02.481
- Jacaerys...
- I am no fool. Mother.

370
00:33:03.691 --> 00:33:05.443
The proof is here for all to see.

371
00:33:08.696 --> 00:33:12.116
Yet I may argue my legitimacy
to succeed you because I have a dragon.

372
00:33:16.329 --> 00:33:18.372
And now you say
you'll strip that from me too.

373
00:33:34.680 --> 00:33:36.974
I mislike all of this. [sniffles]

374
00:33:39.310 --> 00:33:41.145
Then don't pursue it.

375
00:33:49.570 --> 00:33:54.742
But I cannot gainsay that which
the gods have laid before me.

376
00:34:00.248 --> 00:34:02.625
[tense music playing]

377
00:34:14.679 --> 00:34:16.681
[suspenseful music playing]

378
00:34:20.142 --> 00:34:22.812
[Mysaria] Do whatever you must
to see that it finds her.

379
00:34:36.534 --> 00:34:38.536
[indistinct chatter]

380
00:34:39.036 --> 00:34:41.038
[suspenseful music continues playing]

381
00:34:49.630 --> 00:34:50.840
From the queen.

382
00:34:56.679 --> 00:34:58.681
[music continues]

383
00:35:23.706 --> 00:35:25.750
[music intensifying]

384
00:35:37.219 --> 00:35:38.179
[music stops]

385
00:35:38.180 --> 00:35:39.638
[man 1] You won't believe this.

386
00:35:41.766 --> 00:35:45.644
Word is. Rhaenyra's recruiting smallfolk
to go to Dragonstone.

387
00:35:45.728 --> 00:35:48.314
- Oh. fuck that.
- They wouldn't take you anyway.

388
00:35:48.397 --> 00:35:49.648
[all laughing]

389
00:35:49.732 --> 00:35:53.861
Ulf. they're looking
for Targaryen bastards.

390
00:35:55.071 --> 00:35:57.156
Boats leave tonight. Hour of the bat.

391
00:35:57.239 --> 00:36:00.326
Seven Hells. Ulf. This is it!

392
00:36:00.409 --> 00:36:03.412
Yeah. a likely story.
You've been taken in. lads.

393
00:36:03.496 --> 00:36:06.665
No. no. no. The queen's own handmaid
is here spreading the word.

394
00:36:07.249 --> 00:36:09.460
Well. that's a shame.
'cause I'd have been first in line

395
00:36:09.543 --> 00:36:12.671
if it wasn't for my injury.
'cause my leg hasn't been the same since...

396
00:36:12.755 --> 00:36:15.841
Are you touched?
He's saying you can claim a dragon!

397
00:36:15.925 --> 00:36:18.260
[man 1] The barkeep
from the Seven Maesters is going.

398
00:36:18.344 --> 00:36:21.514
And two of the girls from Mother's.
A chance to stick it to Aemond!

399
00:36:21.597 --> 00:36:23.808
- And claim a dragon.
- A dragon!

400
00:36:23.891 --> 00:36:25.518
- Yeah. no. I know.
- [man 1] Wha...?

401
00:36:25.601 --> 00:36:27.228
I know. I just... I can't...

402
00:36:28.521 --> 00:36:30.398
I can't be sure it's all true.

403
00:36:34.276 --> 00:36:39.031
You can't mean that you've been drinking
at the expense of all these...

404
00:36:39.115 --> 00:36:41.659
- These good people. for a fiction? No...
- No. No. Shh.

405
00:36:41.742 --> 00:36:44.036
All spark and no tinder?

406
00:36:44.120 --> 00:36:45.764
- [man 1] They won't be happy.
- [man 2] Very unhappy.

407
00:36:45.788 --> 00:36:47.915
- Never live it down.
- Never live it down.

408
00:36:47.998 --> 00:36:50.251
- Come on. Ulf! The time has come!
- [man 1] Come on!

409
00:36:50.334 --> 00:36:51.836
[man 2] Can I see a little glimmer?

410
00:36:51.919 --> 00:36:52.962
[man 1] Where is it?

411
00:36:53.045 --> 00:36:55.047
- There's the Ulf I know.
- [man 1] Yes.

412
00:36:55.131 --> 00:36:57.925
- [man 2] There it is! There it is! Hey!
- Yes. there he is! Yes! Yes!

413
00:36:58.008 --> 00:37:00.052
Wine! Wine for Ulf the Dragonlord!

414
00:37:00.136 --> 00:37:01.595
Ulf the Dragonlord!

415
00:37:01.679 --> 00:37:04.473
- [patrons cheering]
- Ulf! Ulf the Dragonlord!

416
00:37:04.557 --> 00:37:06.267
- Ulf the Dragonlord!
- Ulf the Dragon!

417
00:37:06.350 --> 00:37:08.352
[all chanting wildly] <i>Ulf. Ulf. Ulf...!</i>

418
00:37:12.022 --> 00:37:13.899
[laughing]

419
00:37:17.486 --> 00:37:19.280
[woman] I don't want you to go.

420
00:37:20.156 --> 00:37:21.574
I have to. Kat.

421
00:37:21.657 --> 00:37:26.287
We'll go to my brother in Tumbleton.
They'll have food. You'll find work.

422
00:37:26.370 --> 00:37:27.705
I can't ignore this.

423
00:37:32.501 --> 00:37:34.044
I never knew my father.

424
00:37:36.630 --> 00:37:37.756
That much is true.

425
00:37:42.887 --> 00:37:44.388
But I did know my mother.

426
00:37:57.526 --> 00:38:01.405
I hid it from you.
And I'm sorry for that.

427
00:38:06.160 --> 00:38:07.161
She worked...

428
00:38:09.079 --> 00:38:10.289
in a pleasure house.

429
00:38:12.124 --> 00:38:16.295
She was granted more freedom than most
because of who she was.

430
00:38:19.757 --> 00:38:22.801
And because rich men pay more
to fuck a woman with silver hair.

431
00:38:27.389 --> 00:38:28.682
She used to tell me...

432
00:38:30.643 --> 00:38:33.395
I was no different
to her brother's boys...

433
00:38:35.981 --> 00:38:38.526
Viserys and Daemon.

434
00:38:44.782 --> 00:38:46.283
But I was ashamed of her.

435
00:38:49.912 --> 00:38:52.206
I tried to make my way
with my own hands.

436
00:38:54.333 --> 00:38:56.335
[somber music playing]

437
00:38:57.586 --> 00:38:59.171
I could not protect you.

438
00:39:00.589 --> 00:39:03.425
I could not keep our girl alive.

439
00:39:11.058 --> 00:39:12.142
And now...

440
00:39:14.186 --> 00:39:19.483
we would never want again
if I claimed a dragon.

441
00:39:21.569 --> 00:39:22.987
They'd make you a lady.

442
00:39:29.118 --> 00:39:31.745
I do not care to be a lady.
Hugh.

443
00:39:34.665 --> 00:39:36.792
And neither do I want to be
a widow.

444
00:39:45.050 --> 00:39:46.510
I have to do something.

445
00:39:48.262 --> 00:39:50.264
[dramatic music playing]

446
00:40:18.792 --> 00:40:20.794
[melancholy music playing]

447
00:42:26.795 --> 00:42:28.714
[dragonkeeper in High Valyrian]

448
00:42:30.174 --> 00:42:32.509
[in High Valyrian]

449
00:42:32.593 --> 00:42:34.887
[dragonkeeper in High Valyrian]

450
00:43:22.643 --> 00:43:24.645
[dragon growls]

451
00:43:47.668 --> 00:43:51.505
[in English] I used to think I knew
what it was to claim a dragon. but...

452
00:43:56.510 --> 00:44:00.764
I understand now that
what I thought I knew is ash in the wind.

453
00:44:14.027 --> 00:44:17.197
Perhaps it is blood. Or worth.

454
00:44:18.824 --> 00:44:20.325
Or perhaps it's something else.

455
00:44:25.831 --> 00:44:31.295
Each of you has left behind a life
to answer this call.

456
00:44:32.671 --> 00:44:36.967
A life to which you
might never return.

457
00:44:39.469 --> 00:44:42.139
If you survive.
you will be transformed.

458
00:44:43.891 --> 00:44:47.561
No man or woman can face a dragon
and be otherwise.

459
00:44:53.358 --> 00:44:56.945
Some of you may welcome
the prospect of change.

460
00:44:57.029 --> 00:45:00.324
even death. given the alternatives:

461
00:45:01.074 --> 00:45:04.870
privation. starvation. war.

462
00:45:06.288 --> 00:45:10.709
This is our purpose.
To end those hardships.

463
00:45:12.836 --> 00:45:13.879
For you.

464
00:45:15.797 --> 00:45:18.467
For your kin. For all the realm.

465
00:45:20.302 --> 00:45:24.473
With these two dragons added
to our number.

466
00:45:24.556 --> 00:45:26.683
the enemy will have no choice
but to give way.

467
00:45:28.310 --> 00:45:30.812
And peace will be restored.

468
00:45:33.690 --> 00:45:36.485
Suffering will be ended.

469
00:45:37.319 --> 00:45:41.907
And without bloodshed. gods willing.

470
00:45:44.826 --> 00:45:46.578
[dragon growls]

471
00:45:51.750 --> 00:45:53.752
[tense music playing]

472
00:45:58.048 --> 00:46:01.426
The dragon named Vermithor...

473
00:46:03.971 --> 00:46:07.307
is the largest in the world after Vhagar

474
00:46:07.391 --> 00:46:10.602
and perhaps the most fierce.

475
00:46:15.357 --> 00:46:17.025
He's called the Bronze Fury.

476
00:46:23.699 --> 00:46:24.950
We will go to him now.

477
00:46:27.494 --> 00:46:28.495
And...

478
00:46:32.332 --> 00:46:33.917
may the gods bless you.

479
00:47:13.331 --> 00:47:15.667
[in High Valyrian]

480
00:47:25.385 --> 00:47:26.720
[thudding]

481
00:47:27.888 --> 00:47:29.890
[rumbling]

482
00:47:36.646 --> 00:47:38.648
[dragon growling]

483
00:47:40.233 --> 00:47:42.861
[rumbling continues]

484
00:47:44.905 --> 00:47:46.448
[heavy footsteps approaching]

485
00:48:03.632 --> 00:48:05.634
[dragon growling]

486
00:48:08.095 --> 00:48:10.097
[roaring]

487
00:48:17.479 --> 00:48:18.897
[Rhaenyra in High Valyrian]

488
00:48:20.190 --> 00:48:22.109
[roars softly]

489
00:48:23.735 --> 00:48:25.737
[dragon grumbling]

490
00:48:28.406 --> 00:48:29.616
[Rhaenyra in High Valyrian]

491
00:48:37.165 --> 00:48:39.167
[growling]

492
00:48:53.473 --> 00:48:55.517
[low growling]

493
00:49:01.481 --> 00:49:03.900
[low growling continues]

494
00:49:29.467 --> 00:49:30.969
[growls]

495
00:49:36.433 --> 00:49:38.393
[in English]
Who among you would be first?

496
00:49:39.561 --> 00:49:41.563
[dragonseeds murmuring]

497
00:49:48.737 --> 00:49:50.739
[dragon growling]

498
00:50:07.923 --> 00:50:12.427
[Rhaenyra] I've nothing more to tell you.
It must be the dragon who speaks.

499
00:50:20.852 --> 00:50:22.854
[dragonseeds murmuring]

500
00:50:24.940 --> 00:50:26.983
[murmuring continues]

501
00:50:34.741 --> 00:50:36.743
[dragon growling]

502
00:50:49.631 --> 00:50:51.633
[growling]

503
00:51:03.603 --> 00:51:05.355
- [roaring]
- [dragonseeds gasp and yell]

504
